.TH LLNG-BACKEND-SETUP 8 "December 2024" "pam-llng 1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
llng-backend-setup \- Configure a server as an SSH backend with LemonLDAP::NG
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B llng-backend-setup
.BI \-\-portal " URL"
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B llng-backend-setup
configures a Linux server as an SSH backend that:
.IP \(bu 2
Accepts SSH certificate authentication via LLNG CA
.IP \(bu 2
Creates Unix users automatically from LLNG attributes
.IP \(bu 2
Enables sudo authorization via LLNG
.IP \(bu 2
Uses NSS module for user/group resolution
.PP
Unlike bastion mode, backend mode allows direct shell access and can create
local Unix users on-demand based on LLNG user attributes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-portal " " \fIURL\fR
LemonLDAP::NG portal URL (required).
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-server\-group " " \fINAME\fR
Server group name for authorization rules. Default: default
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-token\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Read server token from file (use - for stdin). For non-interactive enrollment.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-create\-user
Disable automatic user creation.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-sudo
Disable sudo configuration.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-nss
Disable NSS configuration.
.TP
.BR \-\-allow\-password
Allow password authentication (in addition to certificates).
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Non-interactive mode (requires \-\-token\-file).
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-insecure
Skip SSL certificate verification.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be done without making changes.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The script performs the following configuration steps:
.IP 1. 4
Downloads SSH CA public key from LLNG portal (/ssh/ca endpoint).
.IP 2. 4
Creates sshd configuration with TrustedUserCAKeys.
.IP 3. 4
Configures PAM for LLNG authorization with user creation.
.IP 4. 4
Configures sudo to use LLNG authorization.
.IP 5. 4
Configures NSS to resolve users/groups from LLNG.
.IP 6. 4
Enrolls the server with LLNG (unless token provided).
.IP 7. 4
Restarts SSH service.
.SH USER CREATION
When a user authenticates successfully and does not exist locally, the PAM
module can automatically create the user with attributes from LLNG:
.IP \(bu 2
Username from SSH certificate principal
.IP \(bu 2
GECOS from LLNG user attributes
.IP \(bu 2
Home directory created automatically
.IP \(bu 2
Shell from LLNG or system default
.IP \(bu 2
Group memberships from LLNG
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ssh/llng_ca.pub
SSH CA public key downloaded from LLNG.
.TP
.I /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-llng-backend.conf
SSH configuration for backend mode.
.TP
.I /etc/pam.d/sshd
PAM configuration for SSH.
.TP
.I /etc/pam.d/sudo
PAM configuration for sudo.
.TP
.I /etc/security/pam_llng.conf
PAM module configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/nss_llng.conf
NSS module configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/nsswitch.conf
NSS configuration (modified to include llng).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Interactive setup with all features:
.RS
.nf
sudo llng-backend-setup \-\-portal https://auth.example.com
.fi
.RE
.PP
Setup without automatic user creation:
.RS
.nf
sudo llng-backend-setup \-\-portal https://auth.example.com \\
    \-\-no-create-user
.fi
.RE
.PP
Setup with password fallback allowed:
.RS
.nf
sudo llng-backend-setup \-\-portal https://auth.example.com \\
    \-\-allow-password
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Setup completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Setup failed.
